'''''Jonas in the Jungle''''' is a 2013 documentary film by [[Peter Sempel]] about the filmmaker [[Jonas Mekas]].<ref>http://www.filmfesthamburg.de/mobil/en/film/jonas-in-the-jungle/10466</ref> It is part of a long term series of films about Mekas (''[[Jonas in the Desert]]'' (1991), ''[[Jonas at the Ocean]]'' (2004)). The earlier films were focused more on Mekas' work, while this film is more about the life of the 'legend of film avant-garde' as he enters his 90's, still working, and still maintaining relevance in the modern world.

The film also explores the [[Anthology Film Archives]], of which Mekas' was one of the cofounders.<ref>http://anthologyfilmarchives.org/about/about</ref>

The film premiered Oct 3, 2013, in Hamburg, Germany.<ref>http://www.sempel.com/sempel.html</ref>

